51 class PositionVelocity : public State {
52 public:
53  ~PositionVelocity() {}
54  explicit PositionVelocity()
55  : position_(Vector3d::Zero()),
56  velocity_(Vector3d::Zero()) {}
57  explicit PositionVelocity(double x, double y, double z,
58  double vx, double vy, double vz);
59  explicit PositionVelocity(const Vector3d& position,
60  const Vector3d& velocity);
61  explicit PositionVelocity(const fastrack_msgs::State& msg);
62  explicit PositionVelocity(const VectorXd& config);
63 
64  // Accessors.
65  inline double X() const { return position_(0); }
66  inline double Y() const { return position_(1); }
67  inline double Z() const { return position_(2); }
68  inline double Vx() const { return velocity_(0); }
69  inline double Vy() const { return velocity_(1); }
70  inline double Vz() const { return velocity_(2); }
71 
72  inline Vector3d Position() const { return position_; }
73  inline Vector3d Velocity() const { return velocity_; }
74  inline VectorXd Configuration() const {
75  VectorXd config(3);
76  config(0) = position_(0);
77  config(1) = position_(1);
78  config(2) = position_(2);
79 
80  return config;
81  }
82 
83  // Setters.
84  inline double& X() { return position_(0); }
85  inline double& Y() { return position_(1); }
86  inline double& Z() { return position_(2); }
87  inline double& Vx() { return velocity_(0); }
88  inline double& Vy() { return velocity_(1); }
89  inline double& Vz() { return velocity_(2); }
90 
91  inline Vector3d& Position() { return position_; }
92  inline Vector3d& Velocity() { return velocity_; }
93 
94  // Compute the relative state to a particular planner state.
95  template<typename PS>
96  PositionVelocity RelativeTo(const PS& planner_x) const {
97  return PositionVelocity(position_ - planner_x.Position(),
98  velocity_ - planner_x.Velocity());
99  }
100 
101  // Compute the relative state to a particular configuration.
102  PositionVelocity RelativeTo(const VectorXd& planner_config) const {
103  return RelativeTo<PositionVelocity>(PositionVelocity(planner_config));
104  }
105 
106  // What are the positions that the system occupies at the current state.
107  // NOTE! For simplicity, this is a finite set. In future, this could
108  // be generalized to a collection of generic obstacles.
109  std::vector<Vector3d> OccupiedPositions() const;
110 
111  // Convert to ROS message.
112  fastrack_msgs::State ToRos() const;
113 
114  // Dimension of the state and configuration spaces.
115  static constexpr size_t StateDimension() { return 6; }
116  static constexpr size_t ConfigurationDimension() { return 3; }
117

121  static VectorXd GetConfigurationLower();

123
